<title>ITALY: Italy's Naples sees August CPI up 3.4 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Italy's Naples sees August CPI up 3.4 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>NAPLES, Italy 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Naples said its August consumer price index stood at +0.1 percent month-on-month and +3.4 percent year-on-year.</p>
<p>In July, Naples' inflation rate fell 0.3 percent but grew 3.6 percent year on year respectively.</p>
<p>Naples is one of 10 Italian cities publishing inflation data yesterday and today.</p>
<p>The city's CPI has a weighting of 6.74 percent on the national index. The 10 sample cities have a combined weighting of 69.67 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>Following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to July 1996):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		     0.1   (-0.3)    3.4  (3.6)</p>
<p>    Food				  0.2    (0.1)    4.8  (4.6)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   0.0    (0.0)    1.9  (1.9)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   0.7   (-2.5)    7.6  (0.1)</p>
<p>    Furniture			   0.1    (0.1)    2.0  (4.1)</p>
<p>    Health services		   0.0   (-0.2)    1.9  (1.8)</p>
<p>    Transportation		    0.1    (0.2)    8.8  (9.4)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture     0.1   (-0.5)    2.2  (2.8)</p>
<p>    Education			   0.0    (0.1)    0.2  (0.2)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	  0.1    (0.0)    4.4  (4.9)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	 0.1    (0.0)    2.0  (2.2)</p>
<p>-- Rome newsroom ++396 678 2501</p>
